©FROM MR WILBERFORCE'S DIARY

1787

AT LENGTH
I WELL REMEMBER AFTER A CONVERSATION WITH MR. PITT IN THE OPEN
AIR AT THE ROOT OF AN OLD TREE AT HOLWOOD
JUST ABOVE THE STEEP DESCENT INTO THE VALE 
OF KESTON, I RESOLVED TO GIVE NOTICE 
ON A FIT OCCASION IN THE HOUSE OF COMMONS 
OF MY INTENTION 
TO BRING FORWARD THE ABOLITION 
OF THE SLAVE TRADE

ERECTED BY EARL STANMORE 1862
 BY AUTHORISATION OF EARL STANWORTH."Æ
